                            TRUST BENEFITS
                        </span>

                        <h2 class="mb-5 wow fadeInUp">
                            Why Establish a Trust?
                        </h2>

                        <p class="roboto wow fadeInUp">
                            Trusts are powerful legal tools designed to help individuals and families protect their assets,
                            maintain privacy, and ensure a smooth transfer of wealth. Whether you are planning for the future
                            or protecting what you have built, trusts provide a reliable and structured solution.
                        </p>

                    </div>

                    <!-- ACCORDION SECTION -->
                    <div class="accordion-section">

                        <!-- BENEFITS -->
                        <div class="accordion-single accsingle mb-5 wow fadeInUp">
                            <h5 class="header-area d-flex justify-content-between">

                                <button class="accordion-btn w-100 text-start" type="button">
                                    Key Benefits
                                    <span class="accordion-icon ms-auto">+</span>
                                </button>

                            </h5>

                            <div class="content-area">
                                <div class="content-body">

                                    <ul class="roboto">
                                        <li class="mb-3">
                                            • <strong>Privacy Protection:</strong>
                                            Trusts keep your financial matters private, unlike probate proceedings.
                                        </li>

                                        <li class="mb-3">
                                            • <strong>Control Over Distribution:</strong>
                                            Decide how and when your assets are distributed to beneficiaries.
                                        </li>

                                        <li class="mb-3">
                                            • <strong>Probate Avoidance:</strong>
                                            Assets held in a trust can bypass lengthy probate processes.
                                        </li>

                                        <li class="mb-3">
                                            • <strong>Asset Protection:</strong>
                                            Certain trust structures can help protect assets from legal claims.
                                        </li>

                                        <li class="mb-3">
                                            • <strong>Wealth Preservation:</strong>
                                            Helps ensure long-term financial stability for future generations.
                                        </li>

                                        <li>
                                            • <strong>Efficient Estate Management:</strong>
                                            Simplifies administration and reduces complications for your family.
                                        </li>
                                    </ul>

                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <!-- LONG TERM -->
                        <div class="accordion-single accsingle mb-5 wow fadeInUp">
                            <h5 class="header-area d-flex justify-content-between">

                                <button class="accordion-btn w-100 text-start" type="button">
                                    Long-Term Advantages
                                    <span class="accordion-icon ms-auto">+</span>
                                </button>

                            </h5>

                            <div class="content-area">
                                <div class="content-body">

                                    <p class="roboto mb-4">
                                        Trust planning goes beyond immediate protection. It creates a long-term framework
                                        for managing wealth across generations while preserving your legacy intentions.
                                    </p>

                                    <ul class="roboto">
                                        <li>• Multi-generational wealth planning</li>
                                        <li>• Structured inheritance for beneficiaries</li>
                                        <li>• Reduced family disputes through clear instructions</li>
                                        <li>• Flexibility in managing complex assets</li>
                                    </ul>

                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <!-- WHO SHOULD CONSIDER -->
                        <div class="accordion-single accsingle mb-5 wow fadeInUp">
                            <h5 class="header-area d-flex justify-content-between">

                                <button class="accordion-btn w-100 text-start" type="button">
                                    Who Should Consider a Trust?
                                    <span class="accordion-icon ms-auto">+</span>
                                </button>

                            </h5>

                            <div class="content-area">
                                <div class="content-body">

                                    <p class="roboto mb-4">
                                        Trusts are not only for high-net-worth individuals. They are beneficial
                                        for anyone seeking clarity, protection, and control over their assets.
                                    </p>

                                    <ul class="roboto">
                                        <li>• Individuals with real estate or investments</li>
                                        <li>• Business owners</li>
                                        <li>• Families planning for future generations</li>
                                        <li>• Individuals with digital or cryptocurrency assets</li>
                                        <li>• Anyone seeking privacy and structured estate planning</li>
                                    </ul>

                                </div>
                            </div>
